  "doc_id": "55652",
  "text": "Relatively high losses to follow-up also limit what can be learnt from our review. Of children not found at 6-24 months post-treatment, some will have died, some will be alive but unwell or still malnourished, and some will be alive and well [CITATION_1] . What percentage are in each category is likely to vary programme to programme, but what is almost certain is that known mortality and morbidity are underestimates of the true value.",
